The change logic looks good to me. One minor suggestion, why not put the commands into a bash script and run the script instead of running it in batches? If there are too many ip addr in the list, that can result in multiple SSH and multiple calls.

> The change logic looks good to me. One minor suggestion, why not put the commands into a bash script and run the script instead of running it in batches? If there are too many ip addr in the list, that can result in multiple SSH and multiple calls.

Is your suggestion to create a file with the batched up commands on the duthost first and then make one call to `shell` to execute that file? I figured this would be overkill as more than likely this will only execute the `shell` command 1-4 times.

Also there is already a precedent of doing it this way here: https://github.com/sonic-net/sonic-mgmt/pull/8126

Update: I checked the timestamps of the calls in the test, all the time is spent in orchagent updating the routes, so I don't think removing the multiple shell calls will save us much time:

Test triggers first batch
```
28/05/2025 17:31:44 base._run L0071 DEBUG | /data/tests/common/devices/sonic_asic.py::shell#580: [qzq203] AnsibleModule::shell, args=["\n \n \n \n \n for s in 2.0.0.1 <snip>
```

Duthost receives ansible request and spends time processing neighbors:
```
2025 May 28 17:31:44.218468 qzq203 INFO python[20541]: ansible-ansible.legacy.command Invoked with _raw_params=#012 #012 #012 #012 #012 for s in 2.0.0.1 <snip>
2025 May 28 17:31:44.225972 qzq203 NOTICE swss#orchagent: :- addNeighbor: Created neighbor ip 2.0.0.1, 11:22:33:44:55:66 on PortChannel2001
2025 May 28 17:31:44.226678 qzq203 NOTICE swss#orchagent: :- addNextHop: Created next hop 2.0.0.1 on PortChannel2001
<snip>
2025 May 28 17:32:01.416682 qzq203 NOTICE swss#orchagent: :- addNeighbor: Created neighbor ip 2.0.35.40, 11:22:33:44:55:66 on PortChannel2001
2025 May 28 17:32:01.417084 qzq203 NOTICE swss#orchagent: :- addNextHop: Created next hop 2.0.35.40 on PortChannel2001
```

Test triggers next batch:
```
28/05/2025 17:32:01 base._run L0071 DEBUG | /data/tests/common/devices/sonic_asic.py::shell#580: [qzq203] AnsibleModule::shell, args=["\n \n \n \n \n for s in 2.0.35.41 <snip>
```
